  /*
    Weâ€™re working with a server that has 27 databases. 
We have a dbo.Products table in a Widgets database with columns ProductId, ProductName, Description, Price, and Created, which is a datetime field.

Exercise #1: Write a query to return the id and name for products that cost more than $10.99 and contain the word "waffle" in the description.
    */

SELECT 
    ProductID, ProductName
FROM
    dbo.Products
WHERE
    Price > 10.99
AND
    Description = %waffle%
;
